    "title": "New York City sues drug companies over opioid epidemic",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "NEW YORK, Jan 23 (Reuters) - New York City said on Tuesday it has sued several companies that make or distribute prescription opioids, seeking to hold them accountable for their role in what it called a deadly epidemic afflicting the city.\nMayor Bill de Blasio announced the lawsuit, saying it seeks to recoup $500 million of costs to combat the epidemic.\nAmong the defendants are manufacturers such as Allergan Plc , Johnson & Johnson, Purdue Pharma LP and Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd, and distributors such as AmerisourceBergen Corp, Cardinal Health Inc and McKesson Corp, the city said. (Reporting by Jonathan Stempel in New York; Editing by Tom Brown)\n ",
